ionalism\">Functionalism</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Conflict_theories\" title=\"Conflict theories\">Conflict theories</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Middle_range_theory_(sociology)\" title=\"Middle range theory (sociology)\">Middle-range</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Mathematical_sociology\" title=\"Mathematical sociology\">Mathematical sociology</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Critical_theory\" title=\"Critical theory\">Critical theory</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Social_constructionism\" title=\"Social constructionism\">Social constructionism</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Structuralism\" title=\"Structuralism\">Structuralism</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Interactionism\" title=\"Interactionism\">Interactionism</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Base_and_superstructure\" title=\"Base and superstructure\">Base and superstructure</a></td></li></ul>\n</tr><tr><th class=\"navbox-abovebelow\" style=\"padding:0.1em\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Social_research\" title=\"Social research\">Methods</a></th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em;padding-top:0.2em;\">\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/wiki/Quantitative_research\" title=\"Quantitative research\">Quantitative</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Qualitative_research\" title=\"Qualitative research\">Qualitative</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Comparative_historical_research\" title=\"Comparative historical research\">Historical</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Computational_sociology\" title=\"Computational sociology\">Computational</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Ethnography\" title=\"Ethnography\">Ethnography</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Ethnomethodology\" title=\"Ethnomethodology\">Ethnomethodology</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/wiki/Social_network_analysis\" title=\"Social network analysis\">Network analysis</a></td></li></ul>\n</tr><tr><th class=\"navbox-abovebelow\" style=\"padding:0.1em\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Subfields_of_sociology\" title=\"Subfields of sociology\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Subfields</a></th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0